---
import CardSection from "../IntegralAsphalt/CardSection.astro";
import TwoColumnSection from "../unitComponents/TwoColumnSection.astro";
import Tred from "../../assets/images/AsphaltStorage/redT.webp";
import FPH1 from "../../assets/images/FuelPreHeaters/FPH1.webp";
import FPH2 from "../../assets/images/FuelPreHeaters/FPH2.webp";
import FPH2Low from "../../assets/images/FuelPreHeaters/Low/FPH2Low.webp";
import FPH3 from "../../assets/images/FuelPreHeaters/FPH3.webp";
import fIcon from "../../assets/images/FuelPreHeaters/FlamaIcon.svg";
import img1 from "../../assets/images/Burners/10.webp";
import FPHPlanos from "./FPHPlanos";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
---

<section class="w-full font-bold mt-20 flex flex-col">
  <div
    class="w-full max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 pb-10"
  >
    <div class="w-full flex flex-col gap-10">
      <div class="w-full">
        <video
          class="w-full rounded-lg"
          playsinline
          controls
          poster="/Gallery/customdes.webp"
          preload="metadata"
          width="1280"
          height="720"
        >
          <source src="/Videos/Webm/bprov1.webp" type="video/webm" />
          <source src="/Videos/Mp4/bprov1.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
        </video>
      </div>
      <div class="w-full">
        <h1 class="text-center font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl">
          No Smoke <br />No Residue <br /> No Early Failure
        </h1><br />
        <p
          class="text-sm text-center lg:text-start lg:text-lg md:text-lg font-thin text-grisT"
        >
          Unheated fuel often results in incomplete combustion, producing smoke
          and leaving unburned droplets. These contaminate the asphalt mix,
          shorten pavement life, and create environmental and odor issues.
          Preheating eliminates all of these issues .
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full flex items-end">
      <Image src={FPH3} alt="Fuel pre-heater system" class="rounded-lg" />
    </div>
  </div>
  <TwoColumnSection
    leftBg="bg-redBg"
    rightBg="bg-blueMain"
    imageSrc={Tred.src}
    imageAlt="Red T icon"
    imageWidth="150px"
  >
    <div slot="left" class="flex flex-col justify-center gap-3">
      <h1 class="text-xl md:text-2xl">Protects Your Plant Components</h1>
      <p class="text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg">
        Incomplete combustion causes soot buildup in the burner, clogging in the
        baghouse, and even potential damage to the drum mixer. The preheater
        ensures complete combustion, keeping the system clean and significantly
        reducing maintenance needs.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div slot="right" class="flex flex-col justify-center gap-3">
      <h1 class="text-xl md:text-2xl">
        Use Low-Cost Fuels Without <br /> Sacrificing Efficiency
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg">
        Combustion with heavy or low-grade fuels is harder without preheating.
        With fuel preheater, burners can use more affordable fuels while still
        achieve clean combustion—reducing operational costs without compromising
        performance.
      </p>
    </div>
  </TwoColumnSection>

  <div class="w-full pt-10">
    <div
      class="w-full px-8 md:px-52 bg-gradient-to-t from-[#272526] to-bgMain h-[100px]"
    >
    </div>
    <div class="w-full px-8 md:px-52 bg-[#272526] h-[100px]">
      <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-bgBeige text-center">
        Be the only one in the market offering a mix that can't be matched
      </h1>
    </div>
    <div
      class="w-full bg-[#272526] grid grid-cols-1 px-8 md:px-52 gap-10 pt-20 pb-20"
    >
      <div
        class="max-w-7xl grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 justify-center mx-auto gap-6"
      >
        <div class="w-full text-white">
          <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold">
            Lower Emissions, Cleaner Operation
          </h2><br />
          <p class="text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg font-thin">
            Proper atomization through preheating minimizes emissions such as
            CO2, unburned hydrocarbons, and NOx. It’s a cleaner and more
            responsible way to operate—especially important in regions with
            strict environmental regulations.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="w-full text-white">
          <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-end">
            Automatic Safety System for Reliable Operation
          </h2><br />
          <p
            class="text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg font-thin text-end md:text-start"
          >
            The fuel preheater includes a built-in safety system that prevents
            the heating element from activating if there is no fuel in the
            pipeline. This protects the system from overheating, prevents damage
            to components, and ensures safe, efficient operation at all times.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full bg-[#272526] flex flex-col gap-10 relative">
      <div
        class="w-full bg-bgBeige grid grid-cols-1 px-8 md:px-52 py-10 -skew-y-2"
      >
        <div
          class="skew-y-2 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-2 max-w-7xl mx-auto pt-5"
        >
          <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold">
            Inline Electric Heating for Maximum Efficiency
          </h2><br />
          <p class="text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg font-thin">
            The fuel preheater uses an inline electric resistance system capable
            of raising the fuel temperature by 40°C, even at flow rates of up to
            840 liters per hour. This rapid, controlled heating reduces fuel
            viscosity instantly, ensuring proper atomization and clean
            combustion—without delays or external heat sources. It's a compact,
            reliable solution for efficient burner performance from the very
            first second.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div
        class="w-full max-w-7xl mx-auto bg-[#272526] grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 py-10"
      >
        <div class="flex justify-center mx-auto px-8">
          <div class="w-full text-white">
            <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold">
              Improved Fuel Atomization
            </h2><br />
            <p class="text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg font-thin">
              The fuel preheater lowers the viscosity of the fuel, allowing it
              to atomize properly into fine droplets that burn completely. This
              ensures cleaner combustion, better heat transfer, and no leftover
              fuel particles in the mix.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div
        class="absolute bottom-[180px] right-0 lg:bottom-0 lg:right-44 w-[30%] lg:w-1/4 flex justify-center"
      >
        <Image src={FPH1} alt="Fuel pre-heater system " />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="w-full flex justify-center">
    <Image
      src={FPH2}
      alt="Fuel pre-heater installed to the system"
      class="hidden lg:block md:block"
    />
    <Image
      src={FPH2Low}
      alt="Fuel pre-heater installed to the system"
      class="lg:hidden md:hidden"
    />
  </div>
  <div
    class="w-full max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 pb-10 flex flex-col justify-center items-center lg:justify-end lg:items-end"
  >
    <h2
      class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-redBg text-center lg:text-end"
    >
      Standard Equipment, No Added Cost
    </h2>
    <p
      class="text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg font-thin lg:w-1/2 text-center lg:text-end"
    >
      Unlike other manufacturers that sell it as an upgrade, Triaso® includes
      the fuel preheater as standard in all burner-equipped plants since 2014.
      No extra charges—just smarter, more efficient combustion built in.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="w-full max-w-7xl mx-auto pb-5 px-8 flex flex-col gap-6">
    <h1 class="text-black text-xl md:text-2xl">
      The Importance of Fuel Preheaters in your Asphalt Plant
    </h1>
    <div class="w-full flex flex-col justify-end items-start space-y-4">
      <div class="h-0.5 w-1/3 bg-blueMain"></div>
      <div class="h-0.5 w-1/3 bg-redBg ml-10"></div>
    </div>
    <details class="group">
      <summary
        class="cursor-pointer list-none flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center"
      >
        <div>
          <p class="font-thin text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg">
            Modern asphalt plant burners are specifically designed for
            low-viscosity fuels. Diesel, being low in viscosity, burns
            efficiently but comes at a high cost. In contrast, the lower the
            cost of the fuel, the higher its viscosity tends to be—making it
            more difficult to burn effectively.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex justify-center items-center">
          <svg
            class="transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180"
            width="64"
            height="64"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            ><g id="SVGRepo_bgCarrier" stroke-width="0"></g><g
              id="SVGRepo_tracerCarrier"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"></g><g id="SVGRepo_iconCarrier">
              <path
                d="M5.70711 9.71069C5.31658 10.1012 5.31658 10.7344 5.70711 11.1249L10.5993 16.0123C11.3805 16.7927 12.6463 16.7924 13.4271 16.0117L18.3174 11.1213C18.708 10.7308 18.708 10.0976 18.3174 9.70708C17.9269 9.31655 17.2937 9.31655 16.9032 9.70708L12.7176 13.8927C12.3271 14.2833 11.6939 14.2832 11.3034 13.8927L7.12132 9.71069C6.7308 9.32016 6.09763 9.32016 5.70711 9.71069Z"
                fill="#0F0F0F"></path>
            </g></svg
          >
        </div>
      </summary>
      <div class="pt-10">
        <p class="font-thin text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg">
          To efficiently burn low-cost fuels, it is necessary to heat them
          before combustion in order to reduce their viscosity—a process known
          as preheating. Without preheating, fuel atomization becomes
          inefficient, resulting in many unburned microdroplets and incomplete
          combustion. This is especially important because the cheaper the fuel,
          the more difficult it is to burn properly.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <Image
      src={img1}
      alt="Importance of usage of a pre-heater system"
      class="rounded-lg"
    >
      <p class="font-thin text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg">
